[
    {
        "content": "<p>Is it possible to have a class instance inside a structure? E.g., something like:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">structure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">deq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DecidableEq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">DecidableEq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">else</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">-- works</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">else</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n<span class=\"c1\">-- failed to synthesize Decidable (a = b)</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Why can't the class inference system find <code>foo.deq</code> when defining <code>bar'</code>, and what would be the correct way to do this?</p>",
        "id": 548167447,
        "sender_full_name": "Yannick Seurin",
        "timestamp": 1761920144
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">import</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Mathlib</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">structure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"n\">deq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">DecidableEq</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">α</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">attribute</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"kn\">instance</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">deq</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Foo</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">bar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">foo</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ℕ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"k\">if</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">then</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">else</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">0</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>you need to explicitly instruct Lean to register the instance using <code>attribute [instance] Foo.deq</code></p>",
        "id": 548167695,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1761920202
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>just because it's \"there\" doesn't mean  Lean will automatically use it</p>",
        "id": 548167752,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1761920216
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but I believe there has been discussions about possibly changing this by allowing attributes in a structure</p>",
        "id": 548167865,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1761920240
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Great, thanks! ChatGPT gave me 5 different answers (3 of which were wrong), but not this one <span aria-label=\"sweat smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f605\" role=\"img\" title=\"sweat smile\">:sweat_smile:</span></p>",
